# Code Standards for React Components

## General Principles
- Write self-explanatory code rather than relying on comments
- Use meaningful variable names that make the purpose clear
- Extract complex logic into well-named variables before using in JSX
- Follow a functional programming style where possible

## React Components
- Extract complex rendering logic into separate variables
- Use short, descriptive variable names for props destructuring
- Keep components focused on a single responsibility

## Conditional Rendering
- Use map constants for conditional component rendering instead of multiple conditional checks in JSX
- Define component maps at the top level, outside of component functions
- Use enums as keys for type safety in component maps
- Follow the pattern: `const COMPONENT_MAP: Record<EnumType, () => ReactElement>`
- Access map values by key: `{COMPONENT_MAP[someEnum]()}`

## Component Organization
- Place each component in its own folder at the same level within the components directory
- Avoid nested component hierarchies unless absolutely necessary
- Never use index.ts barrel files - import components directly from their source
- Follow the pattern: `import ComponentName from "../components/ComponentName/ComponentName"`

## Tooltips
- Set both overlayMinWidth and overlayMaxWidth to the same value
- Use proper semantic HTML structure within tooltips (headings, paragraphs)
- Always provide a title for tooltips 
